%% TrustyAI Explainability - Data Flow Diagram
%% Generated by: Claude Opus 4.6
sequenceDiagram
    participant MM as ModelMesh Runtime
    participant KS as KServe InferenceService<br/>(via Knative)
    participant TrustyAI as TrustyAI Service<br/>8080/TCP HTTP
    participant Storage as Storage Backend<br/>(PVC/MariaDB/MinIO)
    participant ModelServer as Model Server<br/>gRPC KServe v2
    participant Prom as Prometheus<br/>80/TCP HTTP
    participant Client as Client / Dashboard

    Note over MM,TrustyAI: Flow 1: ModelMesh Inference Payload Ingestion
    MM->>TrustyAI: POST /consumer/kserve/v2<br/>80/TCP HTTP, No Auth
    TrustyAI->>TrustyAI: InferencePayloadReconciler<br/>reconciles input/output pairs
    TrustyAI->>Storage: Store inference record<br/>Local/JDBC/S3

    Note over KS,TrustyAI: Flow 2: KServe CloudEvent Inference Ingestion
    KS->>TrustyAI: CloudEvent<br/>org.kubeflow.serving.inference.request<br/>8080/TCP HTTP
    KS->>TrustyAI: CloudEvent<br/>org.kubeflow.serving.inference.response<br/>8080/TCP HTTP
    TrustyAI->>TrustyAI: KServeInferencePayload<br/>Reconciler
    TrustyAI->>Storage: Store inference record<br/>Local/JDBC/S3

    Note over TrustyAI,Prom: Flow 3: Scheduled Fairness/Drift Metric Computation
    TrustyAI->>TrustyAI: PrometheusScheduler<br/>(cron trigger)
    TrustyAI->>Storage: Read inference data
    Storage-->>TrustyAI: Dataset
    TrustyAI->>TrustyAI: Compute SPD/DIR/drift metrics
    TrustyAI->>TrustyAI: Publish to Micrometer registry
    Prom->>TrustyAI: GET /q/metrics<br/>80/TCP HTTP, Bearer Token
    TrustyAI-->>Prom: trustyai_spd, trustyai_dir, etc.

    Note over Client,ModelServer: Flow 4: Explainability Request (disabled in RHOAI)
    Client->>TrustyAI: POST /explainers/local/lime<br/>80/TCP HTTP, No Auth
    TrustyAI->>Storage: Load inference data
    Storage-->>TrustyAI: Dataset
    TrustyAI->>ModelServer: ModelInfer RPC<br/>gRPC/HTTP2, plaintext
    ModelServer-->>TrustyAI: Inference response
    TrustyAI->>TrustyAI: Compute LIME explanation
    TrustyAI-->>Client: JSON explanation result

    Note over Client,TrustyAI: Ad-hoc Fairness/Drift Metric Request
    Client->>TrustyAI: POST /metrics/group/fairness/spd<br/>80/TCP HTTP, No Auth
    TrustyAI->>Storage: Read inference data
    Storage-->>TrustyAI: Dataset
    TrustyAI->>TrustyAI: Compute SPD metric
    TrustyAI-->>Client: JSON metric result
